            <bug_when>2009-03-25 17:43:53 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>Maybe it was working before, because it was only applied via the &quot;cursor&quot; property, without any global cursor support.

The thing here is that global cursor changes the stylesheet of the browser to have a global &quot;*&quot; match which enforces a cursor on all elements. This is the only way to apply it while dragging something around. I would say this should work for Opera as well. Would be interesting if this is just some kind of &quot;reflow&quot; issue where Opera do not get the modification as fast as needed or if this is a general issue in the Stylesheet support for Opera.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
